RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 7 7F Dirt CR: 85. Allowance Purse 9600. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE SEPTEMBER 4, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TWO GUNS Let outer rival clear and switched to the two path to vie for the lead between, moved to narrow lead at three-eighths, dueled from that point on with DRAW THE FOUL inside of rival, shook him off at the eighth pole, drew clear holding to the wire. SPEEDING STYLE Cleared off rivals to the rail, backed out from three way battle at the five-sixteenths, jumped back on the bridle at the eighth pole, re-rallied up the inside, second best. DRAW THE FOUL Settled three wide vying for the lead into first turn, narrowly made lead but then assumed duel at the three-eighths pole, continued to battle to the eighth pole where he was fended off, emptied latter stages. ROCKED Stalked right in behind leaders in two path, let top trio get away up backstretch, moved up at the seven-sixteenths pole in the three path, shifted further out turn, minor late foot, never a serious threat. MORE HONOR Trailed clearly early, commenced a mild move at the quarter pole, passed one tiring foe, had nothing left late. TRACK BOUND Tracked in the second flight in the pocket, called upon at the quarter pole, dropped back steadily.

ENTRY.NAME: Track Bound
ENTRY.COMMENT: Tracked in pocket, called upon 1/4, dropped back

ENTRY.NAME: Two Guns
ENTRY.COMMENT: Vied between, duel from 3/8 to 1/8 ins, shook free, cleared

ENTRY.NAME: Speeding Style
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: Cleared rail, back out 5/16, back on bridle 1/8, rallied, 2nd bst

ENTRY.NAME: Rocked
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: Stalk behind leaders, moved up 7/16ths 3p, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: More Honor
ENTRY.COMMENT: Trailed, mild move 1/4, passed one tiring, nothing left late

ENTRY.NAME: Draw the Foul
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w first, to lead 3/8, duel 2w, fended off, emptied late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Pete Selin S. RILLITO RACE 8 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Stakes Purse 20000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS AND UPWARD. No nomination. An entry fee of $250 due at the time of entry. Maidens are least preferred. Same owner entries must prefer a horse at the time of entry. Horses that have started at Rillito have first preference . Second preference by money won in 2022-2023. Weights: 3 years old . 124 Older . 126.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AMAAZA Sent from break, held lead in line of three into first turn, asked for more and opened up on field at the seven-sixteenths pole, never looked back and took out event cozily. CORUSCATION Tracked in four path first turn, maintained position throughout backstretch run, commenced rally at the quarter pole while moving widest of all, gradually gained throughout rally but no match for the winner. COASTAL RUN Set up in line of three into the first turn, leader got away and forced runner to chase foe in three path, fully sent at the five-sixteenths, pursued through lane, nothing left. RED NOON RISING Settled in rear, taken six wide on the far turn, mildly progressed down the stretch. IMA TROUBLE MAKER Tracked on inner paths throughout, ended up in two path while idling on turn, ran evenly through stretch. CHARMANT E Dropped to the rail from the jump, swung out and made three path on the turn, never really asked by rider. NORTH DAWN Vied two wide into the first turn, chased inside of rival after leader stepped out while traveling in the two path, fully ridden at the three-eighths and held position, fully dropped out at the three-sixteenths pole, tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Amaaza
ENTRY.COMMENT: Sent on rail, opened up 7/16ths, cozily

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 9 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 87. Allowance Purse 9600. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MARCH 4, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: A GEM IS A GEM Settled two wide for the run to the first turn, pursued outside, moved to the two path for the stretch, continually gained through the stretch, surged in final stages to win in shadow of the wire. ROYAL JESTER Three wide into first turn, cleared two inner foes to lead at the seven-sixteenths, moved to the rail, ran steadily through the lane trying to fend off lone foe, nipped on wire. FULL DRAW Touch slow from the break, moved three wide on turns, gained steadily on second bend, came home on the wrong lead down the stretch, just got up to finish up the minors. EMPEROR'S CHOICE Stalked in the two path into the first turn, swung out to the five path in move up the backstretch, moved back inside to the two path while progressing on turn, moved to rail for lane, evenly down stretch. IZANAMI Lagged, never fired. NIGHTHAWK SPECIAL Ridden to maintain rail on the lead into the first turn, maintained before dropping back at the three-eighths pole and fading consistently to the wire. KATZUMOTO Taken back into the third flight between rivals into first, never contended.

ENTRY.COMMENT: Lagged, never fired
